{
  "texts": [
    "A table encompassing the number of partition nodes, the number of edges and the density for each bipartite graph is provided in the Supplementary Material (see Sect.",
    "Bipartite graph statisticsMost of the unipartite graph metrics can be extended to the bipartite case [14,98].",
    "Specifically, here we compute the bipartite variants of network statistics such as degree centrality, closeness centrality and betweenness centrality [98,99].The degree centrality of a partition node is the fraction of the nodes of the other partition connected to it [100].",
    "The closeness centrality of a node [97,98] is determined by calcu-lating its average shortest path distance to all other nodes.",
    "It represents the efficiency of a node to be connected directly to nodes from the other partition and indirectly to nodes from the same partition [101]."
  ]
}